718391f-a.title: Manhattan: 5th Avenue - 75th Street
718391f-a.text:
Central Park: Sailboat Pool, with Fifth Avenue anc 75th Street in
the background. The top of the Carlyle apartment house is just
visible over the roof of the apartment builoing adjoining the
synegogue on Fifth Avenue.
May 17, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.

718395f-a.title: Manhattan: 5th Avenue - 75th Street
718395f-a.text:
(1)
Central Park: Sailboat Pool, with Fifth Avenue, from 75th to 76th
Streets, inclusive, in the background.
May 17, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, another view. The synagogue on the S.E. corner of
76th Street is Temple Beth-El ("House of God').
May 17, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.

718388f-a.title: Manhattan: 5th Avenue - 75th Street (East)
718388f-a.text:
Central Park: A set of 2 views northward across the Sailboat (also
hnown as the Conservatory) Lake and showing buildings lining the eastern
confine of the Park; Fifth Ave. Upon the latter, they progress north-
ward from East 75th Street which appears on the right. The Synagogue
shown is at the S.E. corner of East 76th Street and the Avenue.
May 2, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
